From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: vamos <vamos@vamos>
Subject: usb: dwc3: allow runtime mode switching for host-mode controllers

The DWC3 dual-role switching mechanism (__dwc3_set_mode) cleanly handles
transitions between host and device modes, including xHCI teardown and
gadget init. However, it's only available when dr_mode is OTG.

On platforms where firmware forces dr_mode to "host" but the hardware
supports peripheral mode (e.g., Qualcomm QCS6490 with UEFI-provided DTB),
there's no way to enable USB gadget functions at runtime.

Allow mode switching via debugfs for host-mode controllers by:
1. Initializing the drd_work workqueue in host mode
2. Removing the OTG-only guard in dwc3_set_mode()
3. Removing the OTG-only guard in the debugfs mode write handler

The __dwc3_set_mode worker already handles all transitions correctly
(host_exit -> soft_reset -> gadget_init, and vice versa), so no
additional logic is needed.

---
diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c b/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
index c2ce2f5e60a1..c0aee4216c08 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
@@ -290,9 +290,6 @@ void dwc3_set_mode(struct dwc3 *dwc, u32 mode)
 {
 	unsigned long flags;
 
-	if (dwc->dr_mode != USB_DR_MODE_OTG)
-		return;
-
 	spin_lock_irqsave(&dwc->lock, flags);
 	dwc->desired_dr_role = mode;
 	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&dwc->lock, flags);
@@ -1621,6 +1618,8 @@ static int dwc3_core_init_mode(struct dwc3 *dwc)
 	case USB_DR_MODE_HOST:
 		dwc3_set_prtcap(dwc, DWC3_GCTL_PRTCAP_HOST, false);
 
+		INIT_WORK(&dwc->drd_work, __dwc3_set_mode);
+
 		if (dwc->usb2_phy)
 			otg_set_vbus(dwc->usb2_phy->otg, true);
 		for (i = 0; i < dwc->num_usb2_ports; i++)
diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc3/debugfs.c b/drivers/usb/dwc3/debugfs.c
index d18bf5e32cc8..0892ef8d810c 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc3/debugfs.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc3/debugfs.c
@@ -445,9 +445,6 @@ static ssize_t dwc3_mode_write(struct file *file,
 	if (copy_from_user(&buf, ubuf, min_t(size_t, sizeof(buf) - 1, count)))
 		return -EFAULT;
 
-	if (dwc->dr_mode != USB_DR_MODE_OTG)
-		return count;
-
 	if (!strncmp(buf, "host", 4))
 		mode = DWC3_GCTL_PRTCAP_HOST;
 
